It’s trash, actually. Michael Keaton, you will always be famous.
Really glad I didn’t watch this movie until I was in my 30s and also hating working a 9-5. There’s no way I’d have found it this humorous if I watched it as a teen. Also, Milton I would die for you!
Personally, I would appreciate a group of people hyping me up before a gynecology appointment.
